the game is more riddled with bots and hackers than tf2;
epic bought the studio that made this game and delisted it from steam;
the clones are funnier than this, as most of them don't have the annoying grab mechanics.

going free to play cause you couldn't figure out how to keep the game fresh and focusing too hard on the skins feels like a sellout

if youre starting from the Free to play era theres nothing wrong with the game, just kind of shitty to the people that bought it at some point to find out your purchase was p-much worthless :)

TLDR: Game good, if a little repetetive, but i dont agree with decisions made by the company

going f2p soon so dont bother buying it. unless you want it on steam, because its also being removed from steam (though still playable if you already own it) as soon as it goes free to play. if you play it on linux like me (or steam deck) then theres no guarantees itll keep supporting linux compatibility once it goes epic games store only since egs itself doesnt even officially support linux. obviously theres ways around that to install egs games on linux but still theres no guarantee theyll keep linux support for the anticheat much longer

dont personally have anything against using a different launcher or installer or whatever but itll be real annoying if the game suddenly stops working on my pc because they decide to uncheck the one (1) box that lets eac work on linux. then itll really feel like ive wasted my money :(

if youre in the same boat and like me havent rly played the game since launch then i recommend at least opening up the game to make sure your epic account is linked so even if you have to play it on a different platform you wont lose your old progress or anything (i hope)

Was a funny and entertaining game until they forced you to link with EPIC account.  
Now you can't play the game anymore, like you could when the conditions were different at the time of purchase.
@STEAM:  Please refund my money, the game is no longer playable for me and the conditions to use the game were changed onesided from you. For changing a contract the agreement must come from both sides.
@EPIC: Get the F U C K out of Steam with your retarded business model you C U N T F A C E S.

Would rate it highly for the derpy entertainment that the game (and mainly snowball survival mode) have given me since it came out

if it, you know, consistently worked anymore... (hooray Epic!)

